Nigerian singer, and songwriter, Timi Dakolo, has lamented over the current state of fuel scarcity and power outage in the country as it has led to service apartments are urging tenants to get generators. The music producer disclosed this on Thursday in a tweet via his official Twitter page, stating that service apartments are canceling the part of their contract that says” no personal generator in the facility.” He wrote, “Nigeria will humble you, service apartment said they are not doing servicing again. Everybody should please get their own generator. “They cancel the contract that says” no personal generator in the facility.”